

    
       A poem written by me, Nikki Leung...Ahem hem hem:  Scour the ocean, land, sky and sea But never will you be able to find me, Look over grass and tree, Wherever you look, I will flee, Oh, how I am so glum, so glum If only I could spread the wings of Freedom! I travel on the lightest breeze, Though the sky, and through the trees, I could run forever and for eternity, I have never experienced jollity, Know you not who I am? I am the Wind...    
    
    
